<item>
            <title>[LU-14923] do not always take write lock for writable mmap</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14923</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, Lustre always takes a PW lock when working with a writable mmap.&#160; This is not great because it means if multiple nodes map the same file writably and do pure read only, they&apos;ll all get write locks.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is pretty easy to fix - just check we are doing a mkwrite when selecting the lock mode.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
